The paper deals with the problem of learning probability distributions from data, which is a central topic in machine learning. The paper also mentions algorithmic learning theory, which is a subfield of machine learning that focuses on the theoretical analysis of learning algorithms. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the computability of probability measures, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and computability theory (cs.DS). The paper also mentions explanatory learning, which is a type of learning that aims to provide explanations for the learned concepts, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
